[h1]v0.1.1 — Engine output slider now actually applies[/h1]

The [b]Engine output[/b] sandbox slider (Drivetrain page, range 0.25–3.0, default 1.0) is now wired into the realism overhaul. The slider existed in 0.1.0 but the value was never multiplied into the engineForce write — moving it had no effect.

Default 1.0 preserves 0.1.0 behaviour exactly. If 60–70 mph top speeds feel too slow, bump it to 1.5 or 2.0 — your cars will pull harder off the line and top out higher.

Only applies when [b]Reference power & weight[/b] is enabled.

[b]No manual install update needed[/b] — Workshop subscription only.
